-- Turkish 12-Month Inflation Forecast Falls to 7.24 Percent, Survey Shows
-- Steve Bryant
-- 2010-07-08T13:33:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/turkish-12-month-inflation-forecast-falls-to-7-24-perent-survey-shows.html

          
          
             Turkish estimates for inflation in 12
months time fell to 7.24 percent from 7.35 percent, the central
bank said in a biweekly survey.  
 Predictions for inflation at the end of this year also
declined, falling to 7.73 percent from 8.01 percent two weeks
earlier, according to the survey of economists and executives
published by the central bank in Ankara today.  
 Turkish economic growth this year was foreseen at 5.4
percent compared with a previous estimate of 5.2 percent, the
bank said.  
